snippet.title: Karnataka ATMs Dry But Raids Throw Up Crores

localized.description:
In the latest episode of Agenda on Campus - the cash ban series, catch the stakeholders of Karnataka talk about the raids on new and old currency notes across the state amounting to nearly 30 crores. Also, the students of St Joseph's College, Bengaluru relate instances of inconvenience caused post cash ban and raise concerns over washout of the winter session of parliament.
Watch full video: http://www.ndtv.com/video/shows/agenda/karnataka-atms-dry-but-raids-throw-up-crores-442560?yt
